The Sophis Network modifications include, but are not limited to:

  - Post-quantum signature scheme (CRYSTALS-Dilithium ML-DSA-44) as the
    only signature primitive at protocol level.
  - RandomX as the proof-of-work algorithm.
  - sVM — sandboxed WASM virtual machine for smart contracts.
  - L1 native token primitives with linear-typed Resource<T> accounting.
  - Phase 3 ZK-Rollup (STARKs + Risc0).
  - Phase 6 self-hosted data availability layer.
  - Phase 9 PQC-native oracle.
  - Address bech32 prefixes (`sophis:`, `sophistest:`, `sophisdev:`,
    `sophissim:`) and the corresponding consensus invariants.
  - Monetary policy (210M SPHS hard cap, smooth long-tailed emission
    curve, no on-chain devfund, no premine).
  - The Operational Boundaries posture (non-custodial reference team,
    no bridge, no privacy primitives in core).

These modifications are Sophis Network original work and are
distributed under Apache 2.0 as part of the combined Work.

